betterquesting:10.desc:8: hello and welcome to Project Equivalence. to get started put your Tome Of Knowledge worth 500 emc into the table, and choose from the many early game ways to generate emc. You can either farm coco beans for a good amount of emc, farm either pumpkins sugarcane or melons for a decent amount of emc, or plant 2x2 jungle trees and twerk them into existence for a decent chunk of emc.

you are going to need to make yourself a elvin gateway for doing anything advanded in botania, your going to need 3 glimmering liging wood, 8 normal living wood and your gate way core to create your multiblock structure, your also going to need 2 mana pools full of mana and natura pylons on those mana pools. it will tka quite a bit of mana to start the portal but once its going it will consume very little mana while it runs. right click the core with your wand when you have a bit of mana to open the portal.

betterquesting:10.desc:8: To Get water in this pack you will need to grab 2 ice from your table then place them into the world and right click with your philosopher's stone to create water. be sure to place them were they create an infinite pool.
To get early game lava in this pack you need to grab obsidian from your table and place it into the world and right click with your philosophers stone to get lava.

Now That you got lava and water you can make an early game cobblestone generator. You will have to mine the cobble at this moment but later you can get extrautills transfer nodes to mine the cobble automatically.
Now that You got some decent Emc Generation you can now make your smeltery.
As soon as you can you should make a mob farm to get mob drops as they are a decent way of generating emc, as well as getting loot bags that have a chance to have great amount of emc.

Now that you have  got a mob farm you can start thinking about automating it. You can either use a mob dropper that drops mobs onto spikes using vector plates or water, or make a box far from your base so that mobs will spawn and use vector plates and the player trap to kill the mobs.

Another upgrade you can do to your mob farm is to use a drop of evil on the farm. You need dirt for the drop of evil to spread and be able to be used. You can either get the drop of evil from killing wither skeletons, or buy farming 125k emc to pull it out of the emc table.

Another Good Way to Generate Emc is to Mine ores to then smelt ingot ingots. the mining dim is a great source of overworld ores. you just need to bring a ton of torches and have a decent pickaxe to mine said ores.
Using bonsai pots you can automate trees early game. You can also automate chorus fruit.
To make demon metal you need to throw gold into a lava well. To make a lava well place nether brick around lava except the top.
The engineering hammer is a vital part of immersive engineering as it's used to create all the multiblocks in the mod.
You will need to make the coke oven to make creosote oil to make treated logs that will be used later in the pack.

Now that you have access to steel you can make yourself a flint and steel to light yourself a netherportal. after you make and light your nether portal mining in the nether is a great source of emc. be sure to explore for a nether fortress for later use.
the nether fortress will be your only place to find wither skeletons to farm, so be sure to be on the look out for one.
To get passive mobs you can make an area of grass and wait for them to spawn, or craft spawn eggs for each passive mob.

By now you might have gotten a few items that don't have emc make a  few chests to store said items, as this will be common with everything you craft. You can use either metal chests or storage drawers to store said items.

Seared stone is made by smelting cobblestone in the smeltery and casting it in the basin. you will need a lot of seared stone later in the pack. you can also use 4 seared bricks and a stone to create one seared stone in a crafting table.
You will need to smelt either glass or sand in the tinkers smeltery to make clear glass which is used to progress within the mods You can also smelt glass in a furnace to get clear glass.
After getting a bit of seared stone  and a gray petal you will be able to make the petal apothecary to start botania.
Your going to want to make a bit of floral fertilizer to get all the botania flowers. Gray flowers are needed to make the petal apothecary.
The pure daisy is needed to make living rock and living wood.

Skystone is made with 250 mb of ender pearls and 250mb of seared stone to make 500mb of skystone. it takes 1k mb to make a skystone block. you will need a ton of skystone to progress in the pack, as it's used to make living rock.
With the creosote oil you have gathered you can make treated logs that will be used for progression later in the pack
Using the skystone you have made you can create living rock using the pure daisy.
With the treated logs you've made you can convert them using the pure daisy to living wood.
No Description
to get more info on botania be sure to make the lexica botania it will have more information on all the items in the mod and addons

Now that you got yourself an elven portal throw your lexica botania into the portal,and be close to the portal or else you might lose the book. You will get knowledge from the elves and learn more about botania and its addons.
Now that you have a source of living rock you need to make the mana pool. It is the heart of botania all your mana your going to generate is going to be stored here.
Now that you have made a bit of mana from your whatever flower you have chosen to generate mana. You need to throw in some base materials into the mana pool with some mana to get there mana variants.

Now that you got some Floral fertilizer you will  need to right click on some grass or dirt to get an assortment of mystical flowers. You will need at least one of each flower. you can then turn them into petals and farm them with bonemeal to grow them and shears to be able to pick them up.

You are going to need a ton of mana to create a single terra steel, like half a mana pool. The terra steel ingot  is made from mana steel, mana diamond, and a mana pearl. If you take them off the plate you lose all the progress. to start the infusion you need 2 sparks one on the plate and one on a source of mana.

Now that you have gotten yourself some mana resources and a source of living rock it's time to make yourself a runic altar. The runic altar is used to make runes for botania. You will need the basic runes for progression so make yourself a bit of them.
You need this plate to create tera steel.
Now that you got the elven portal throw your mana materials into the portal to get yourself the elven variant materials
Now that you’ve got your elvin portal you are going to need to throw in living rock and living wood into the portal to get elven versions

The Endercrafter will be where you make all the machine frames for all the mods in the pack. It takes quite the resources to make it. the endercrafter does not take power to create items it uses time. creating an ender alternator will speed up the crafting process a bit.
To make an ender ingot you will need to take a  elementium  ingot and an ender pearl and craft them together in a crafting table and bam you got yourself an ender ingot
you can earn more hearts by eating differnt types of food at least once. this book will keep track of alll the foods you have eaten or have yet to eat.

Project Red will be your early refined storage storage system. What you are going to want to make to make yourself one of these systems are item responder chips, item extractor chips, item broadcaster chips, item transport pipes, routed junction pipes routed interface pipes,and a routed request pipe.Item responder chips respond to extractor chips when the chips extract items from the attached inventory.The broadcaster chips broadcasts what items are in the inventory the chip is connected to. Chips are put onto pipes connected to a storage block. Item transport pipes are wat send items to and from storage blocks they can only go straight without breaking a bit. A routed junction pipe lets you turn corners and go other directions if there are multiple pipe connections. Routed interface pipes are what the chips get inserted into and are what connect to inventories. The routed request pipe lets you request items from chests that have a routed interface pipe with a broadcaster chip to the routed request pipe.
the end dimension is a great source of emc. the ender dragon will be a problem that will need to be taken care of first or else you wont be able to live long to gain anything of value,

Now that you have reached the end and hopefully have killed the ender dragon you should make and place a way stone in the end, and your base to get back to the end again easier without crafting ender apples. be sure the dragon is dead as he can destroy the waystone and could be trapped in the end.

You can get thaumcraft crystal clusters via emc they cost 16,384 emc each. Another way to get them is by searching in the mining dimension for crystal clusters. These crystal clusters are semi rare in the mining dimension.

To create the thaumonomicon you need to create salis mundus which is made from 3 different crystals, redstone, flint, and a bowl, and then spread the salis mundus onto a bookshelf to make your thaumonomicon.

The research table is going to be your source to gain thaumcraft knowledge.To make the research table you need to have a pair of scribing tools and right click a thaumcraft table with them and boom you got yourself a research table have fun researching!

The arcane workbench will be your crafting table in thaumcraft you will make most your magical tools in this table. To make the arcane workbench you will need to make another salis mundus and sprinkle it onto a normal crafting table.
The crusible is used for creating items in an alchemical way.
The thaumometer is a vital tool used to scan blocks and items for what they are made of.

betterquesting:10.desc:8: The first and only plate that can be hand crafted is the iron plate. to craft the other plates you will have to use either tinkers plate cast or immersive engineering plate press. you can later use the thermal compactor to make plates.

The gaean keystone is were you insert the staff of gaean. the staff of gaean and the keystone will then unlock the erebus portal. the erebus portal is made of stone brick and leaves, It can be made in the nether portal way. The erebus will be a harsh and deadly environment be sure to have good armor and weapons to take on this realm!

The wand of animation is a powerful wand that animated any block in the game. You can use this wand to make passive resource generation with industrial forgoing mob spawners. Each block animated takes a bit of durability be wary not to waste the wand.

The Antlion Overlord is found in the temple deep within the Erebus you will have to find 4 different mini bosses that drop an idol. The mini bosses are found within the maze around the temple..you will need all 4 unique idols dropped by the minibosses in the maze.You will then need to place each idol in the right spot to unlock the ability to fight the Antlion Overlord. The Antlion Overlord is a tough boss and will be a feat worth accomplishing.

Thaumcraft infusion is a hefty process that takes a bit of aspects and items and creates a new item. You will need to have the aspects in thaumic jars next to the infusion altar, and have the items needed to craft the item in pedestals around the altar. Depending on the craft the instability can be unstable and cause the process to fail. To fix this put a ton of candles and mob heads around the altar.

now that you got elven knowledge to unlock extrabotany knowledge you must eat a nightmare fuel to get a spirit fuel, and then place that spirit fuel into a pedestal and right click it with the lexica botania and you will get the knowledge.

To fight the first gai guardian you need to make the arena like shown in the book. The arena must not have anything blocking it or else the fight won't start.To start the fight right click a terrasteel ingot on the active beacon and the fight will start!

This fight is like the first gai guardian but much harder.It is still done in the same arena. It gives more rewards, and to start the fight you must right click a gai spirit ingot on the active beacon.

Gai guardian three is a little special in the way the fight works. You can not use anything from a mod besides extra botany, botania, and vanilla. If you try using any modded item besides those mods they will drop to the floor. I highly suggest getting end game extra botany or botany armor and weapons. I also suggest getting botania potions to buff you in the fight as the fight is very hard.To start the fight you need to right click an active beacon with a nature orb that has 100k natures breath and the fight will start.

This boss is like the gai guardian three you can't use modded items and they will drop on the floor if used. He is way stronger than gai guardian three so be prepared to lose many times.To start the fight right click a Call of the void on the active beacon and the fight will begin.
